Version 4.0.0 (in progress)

* [Bryan Christ] Add vk_screen_t for terminal migration and virtual surfaces.
* [Bryan Christ] Add vk_frame_t, vk_scroller_t, vk_box_t, vk_label_t,
  vk_marquee_t klasses.
* [Bryan Christ] Add _on_recreate hook so widgets auto-repaint after teleport.
* [Bryan Christ] Add vk_screen_evict_pty to SIGSTOP the session leader
  before teleport.
* [Bryan Christ] Add poll_resize for post-teleport terminal size detection.
* [Bryan Christ] Redesign vk_scroller_t as an attachment widget (derives
  from vk_widget_t instead of vk_frame_t). Add vk_window_t. Remove vk_menu_t.
* [Bryan Christ] Add vk_textbox_t multi-line read-only text display with
  word wrap, keyboard scrolling, and scroller attachment support.
* [Bryan Christ] Fix scroller blank canvas overwriting host border when
  content fits viewport (skip-draw semantics).
* [Bryan Christ] Add scroller host support to vk_listbox_t and vk_textbox_t
  (borderless host pattern).
* [Bryan Christ] Rename vk_desktop_t to vk_surface_t across all APIs and docs.
* [Bryan Christ] Add vk_selectbox_t derived from vk_listbox_t with checkbox
  (multi-select) and radio (single-select) modes, ASCII and Unicode glyph
  styles, and scroller attachment support.
* [Bryan Christ] Use WACS_* wide chars for borders and separators instead of
  ACS_* and hardcoded Unicode codepoints (fixes rendering after teleport to
  Linux console TTY).
* [Bryan Christ] Add wallpaper callback support to vk_screen_t.
  vk_screen_refresh now composites automatically: erase, wallpaper, widget
  blit, refresh.
* [Bryan Christ] Fix vk_box_t initial layout not sizing last slot to absorb
  remainder pixels.
* [Bryan Christ] Add convenience macros for widget state (freeze/thaw,
  show/hide, is_visible). Declare all public API functions inline across
  every klass for reduced call overhead.
* [Bryan Christ] Add widget state flags (STATE_VISIBLE, STATE_FROZEN,
  STATE_NORESIZE) as a uint32_t bitfield on vk_widget_t. Add get/set API,
  show/hide convenience functions. Frozen widgets snapshot their canvas
  into a composer window so the display holds while updates continue.
  No-resize widgets reject vk_widget_resize calls.
* [Bryan Christ] Add vk_deck_t z-order manager. Canvas-less widget that
  composites children directly onto its surface during draw. Supports
  add-to-top/bottom, set-top, cycle, and TAB-driven focus rotation.
* [Bryan Christ] Separate VDK from legacy libviper. vdk.h is the single
  public header; non-public sources live in vdk/. VDK source files no
  longer include viper.h. vdk_color_init() is optional; callers who skip
  it handle start_color() and init_pair() themselves. Widgets use
  COLOR_PAIR() with vdk_color_pair() internally (ncurses-native). viper.h
  includes vdk.h for backwards compatibility.
* [Bryan Christ] Make VDK widgets IO-agnostic. Remove built-in kmio handlers
  from all klasses. Add vk_object_set_kmio() and VkKmioFunc typedef so
  applications install their own keystroke handlers at runtime.
* [Bryan Christ] Add optional drop shadows to vk_deck_t via
  vk_deck_set_shadow(). Shadow is an L-shaped strip (right + bottom edge)
  rendered white-on-black, composited per-child in z-order.
* [Bryan Christ] Fix vdk_color_init() pair 0 swap to match legacy libviper
  strategy. Swap white-on-black into index 0 so it maps to the ncurses
  default pair. No color pairs are sacrificed.
* [Bryan Christ] Add VK_FRAME_REVERSE modifier flag for border styles.
  OR it with VK_FRAME_SINGLE, VK_FRAME_DOUBLE, or VK_FRAME_ASCII to draw
  borders in reverse video. Supported by frames, windows, and scrollers.
* [Bryan Christ] Add VkWindowDecorateFunc-based window chrome to demo deck
  windows: title-bar buttons (─ □ ✕) in reverse video flanked by tees that
  match the border style, and a horizontal separator under the heading.
* [Bryan Christ] Fix demo wallpaper callbacks using wbkgd() on the surface
  canvas, which poisoned ncurses pair 0 and caused deck shadows to inherit
  the wallpaper color instead of rendering white-on-black. Wallpaper now
  paints manually with wattron/mvwaddch.
* [Bryan Christ] Add vk_button_t klass. Push button with Win3.1 / VB DOS
  beveled style: WACS_* single-line box with white highlight on top/left
  and black shadow on bottom/right. Bevel inverts on press. Centered
  text, separate pressed color pair, and a press callback. ASCII fallback
  uses +, -, | with the same two-tone color split.
* [Bryan Christ] Add VK_STATE_EXPAND widget state flag (off by default).
  Containers (vk_box_t, vk_frame_t) only resize a child to fill its slot
  when VK_STATE_EXPAND is set. Convenience macro: vk_widget_set_expand().
* [Bryan Christ] Add cascading deck layout to demo. All 5 deck windows
  now stack in a consistent +col,+row direction. The Transport window
  contains a 5-slot horizontal vk_box_t with Play, FF, RW, Stop, and
  Pause buttons. Unicode symbols (▶, », «, ■, ⏸) are prepended when
  the locale supports UTF-8.
* [Bryan Christ] Fix vk_button_t width calculation to use display width
  (wcswidth) instead of byte length so UTF-8 button labels size correctly.
* [Bryan Christ] Add VK_BUTTON_BASIC relief style for Links-style
  single-row buttons: [ text ] with reverse-video brackets on press.
  vk_button_set_relief_style automatically resizes the widget when
  switching between 3D (height 3) and basic (height 1) styles.
* [Bryan Christ] Add keyboard navigation to demo transport buttons
  (Left/Right to move focus, Space to press). Focused button renders
  with A_BOLD highlight. Pressed state persists until another button
  is pressed.
* [Bryan Christ] Add Dialog deck window to demo with OK, Cancel, Help
  buttons using VK_BUTTON_BASIC relief style.
* [Bryan Christ] Add homogeneous/non-homogeneous layout modes to
  vk_box_t. Homogeneous (default) distributes slots evenly and centers
  children. Non-homogeneous sizes each slot to its child's natural
  dimension; VK_STATE_EXPAND children absorb leftover space.
* [Bryan Christ] Add vk_filler_t: a minimal 1x1 blank widget born with
  VK_STATE_EXPAND. Useful as a spacer in non-homogeneous boxes.
* [Bryan Christ] Add vk_input_t single-line text input widget. Supports
  3D sunken relief (VK_FRAME_SINGLE, VK_FRAME_ASCII) and Links-style
  basic relief (VK_BUTTON_BASIC). Full editing API: insert, backspace,
  delete, cursor movement, home/end, clear. Dynamic text buffer with
  optional max length. Horizontal scrolling for text wider than the
  field width.
* [Bryan Christ] Add Input deck window to demo showcasing both 3D and
  basic input styles with a keyboard handler for text editing.
* [Bryan Christ] Add vk_filedialog_t composite widget derived from
  vk_box_t. File browser with path input, scrollable file/directory
  list (listbox or checkbox selectbox for multiselect), vertical
  scrollbar, OK/Cancel button bar, and built-in keyboard navigation.
  Supports VK_FRAME_SINGLE, VK_FRAME_ASCII, and VK_BUTTON_BASIC styles.
* [Bryan Christ] Add vk_filedialog_set_wrap() API for enabling
  wrap-around navigation on scrollable list widgets.
* [Bryan Christ] Replace Dialog and Input deck windows in demo with
  a single Files window showcasing the filedialog widget.

Version 3.1.1

* [Sergei Trofimovich] User "%s" specifier for safety in a couple
  of printf-style functions.

Version 3.1.0

* [Bryan Christ] Create a FASTCOLOR interface which is equivalent
  to pair_content() but avaialbe externally.

Version 3.0.1

* [Bryan Christ] Fixed FASTCOLOR mode which was broken.

Version 3.0.0

* [Bryan Christ] Require ncursesw.  First step in UTF-8 encoding
  for Unicode support.

Version 2.1.8

* [Bryan Christ] Fix color mapping for terminals that support more
  than 64 colors.

Version 2.1.7

* [Bryan Christ] Partial framework for multiple screens.

Version 2.1.6

* [Bryan Christ] Init UTF-8 locale in viper_init(). 

Version 2.1.5

* [Bryan Christ] Removed obsolete kmio hooks because unmanaged windows
  can accompish the same thing more-or-less.

Version 2.1.4

* [Bryan Christ] Fixed a logic bug in resizing of fullscreen windows.
  Cause unmanaged windows to be blitted after doing a recursive window
  blit redraw.

Version 2.1.3

* [Bryan Christ] Allow unmanaged windows to be resized by default.

Version 2.1.2

* [Bryan Christ] Added an API to get metrics of a widget.  Fixed a
  calculation error in menus with frames.

Version 2.1.1

* [Bryan Christ] Added API to get optimum metrics of listbox
  width and height.

Version 2.1.0

* [Bryan Christ] Added vk_menu_t klass.

Version 2.0.4

* [Bryan Christ] Improved window focus behavior on X terms.

Version 2.0.3

* [Bryan Christ] Fix NULL pointer segfault in viper_window_get_top API.

Version 2.0.2

* [Bryan Christ] Created API to get screen_id from a vwnd_t.

Version 2.0.1

* [Bryan Christ] Added external API for vk_widget_resize() which was
  accidentally overlooked.

Version 2.0.0

* [Bryan Christ] Major rewrite with new VK object classes.
  Removed dependencies on FORM and MENU libraries which are
  Ncurses specific.  Revised API uses vwnd_t instead of WINDOW*
  for standard interface handle.  Added framework for multi-screen
  support.

Version 1.7.1

*  [Bryan Christ] Cause GCC to make to strip symbols to produce
   a smaller binary.

Version 1.7.0

*  [Bryan Christ] Make API more intuitive and simplify deck logic.

Version 1.6.1

*  [Bryan Christ] Moved build system to cmake.

Version 1.6.0

*  [Bryan Christ] Completely removed Glib requirements and replaced
   them with Linux linked list and libc analogs.

Version 1.5.0

*  [Bryan Christ] Removed GSList from window event system
   and replaced it with Linux linked list implemenation. 

Version 1.4.6

*  [Bryan Christ] Added workaround to suppress character echo
   which happens over remote (ssh) connections.

Version 1.4.5

*  [Bryan Christ] Added viper_end() function which gracefully
   releases allocated resources

Version 1.4.4

*  Removed BUTTON4* references from viper_gpm.def because
   some older system don't have these defined.

Version 1.4.3

*  Added version string LIBVIPER_VERSION
*  Added custom hook support for viper_kmio_dispatch()
   facilities. 

Version 1.4.2.2

*  Makefile fix

Version 1.4.2.1

*  Makefile fix

Version 1.4.2

*  Added is_cursor_at* function family.
*  Hide cursor when not using GPM or GPM is running
   in a xterm-like emulator.

Version 1.4.1

*  Makefile patch from Ben Sittler to build parallel
	versions of the library (libviper.so/libviper_wide.so)

Version 1.4.0

*  Major rewrite of the keyboard and mouse facilities.
*  The changes to the mouse facilities should enable
   sysmouse on *BSD should anyone care to do the porting
   work.  The sysmouse functionailty is leveraged from 
   ncurses directly.
  
Version 1.3.2

*  fixed some minor build warnings.

Version 1.3.1

*  code testing on x86-64.
*  displaced several screen initialization and screen
   referencing functions and macros in favor of a
   external global called SCREEN_WINDOW.  viper_init() must
   now be explicitly called to initialize the internal
   structures.
*  enabled gcc -O2 optimizations in Makefile and moved to
   C99 standard (mostly for long long int).

Version 1.3.0

*  retooling of several functions to better support feature like
   fullscreen specifiers and NORESIZE state.
*  new windows are created by default with the NORESIZE flag.
*  setting the ground work for (possibly) multiple workspaces.
*  implemented new callback agents for border manipulation.
   the default agents replace the predefined "window-focus" and
   "window-unfocus" events.  it is now safe to override these
   event functions without consequence.
*  much needed code clean-up.
*  setting ground work to move predefined window managment out
   of library and replace with better event framework. 

Version 1.2.3

*  added viper_menu_bind() to aide in reparenting and reshaping
   a standard menu.
*  changed default behavior of msgbox windows and added some
   much needed bugfixes.

Version 1.2.2

*  fixed a bug in viper_form_driver() which cause the cursor to be
   rendered at a incorrect location.
*  fixed a bug in viper_event_del() which caused a segfault.
*  simplified Makefile cflags to _GNU_SOURCE


Version 1.2.1

*  fixed a minor build warning for file dialog source file.

Version 1.2.0

*  added support for a file dialog box
*  added functions to colorize and normalize forms
*  added cursor support to forms
*  fixed a small bug in the viper_forms_destroy() helper
*  added a subwin_move_realign() to help move a nested subwin.  this is
   currently _not_ supported in any curses implementation nor is it
   likely to ever be.
*  bug fix for window_fill() which unfortuately triggered an API change.
*  added API function viper_form_driver() to support forms cursor support.

Version 1.1.1

*  fixed a small, but critical bug which caused viper_menu_destroy() to
   leak memory and crash applications (namely VWM).

Version 1.1

*  moved the support for hotkeys out of libviper and in to VWM (because it
   made more sense :)

*  made GPM functionality optional.  compling libviper with support for GPM
   is now controlled by the definition _VIPER_MOUSE_GPM.  by default, the
   make script enables this flag.  manually edit Makefile to change.

Version 1.0

*  initial release.
